      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE BIT SUPER (7) has a strong record this track and trip with five wins and five placings from 13 starts. Placed last time (19.18) at this track in a NG, finishing second and beaten 5.5 lengths. Expected to go close. SHREWD ETHICS (1) was among the minors three back at this track then missed the frame the last two, but drawn box 1 this time where she has two wins. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. PAW ZEVA (2) is a good beginner but will need a quick break. Latest effort finished 3rd over 440m at Goulburn beaten 4 lengths (25.20) behind Fearless Bandit in a Grade 4/5 on March 27. Looks well placed here and among the chances. SUNNY SUE (3) looks an each-way chance.",
